      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine. This chassis exemplifies 90s lightweight engineering with its near-perfect 50/50 weight distribution and four-wheel double-wishbone suspension. The drivetrain remains robust, utilizing a 5-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. To address common thermal management concerns, the cooling system has been reinforced with a high-capacity aluminum radiator. Compression remains strong across both rotors, ensuring the sequential Hitachi turbos spool efficiently through the primary and secondary transition phases. The interior remains driver-centric, and the exterior retains its iconic 'organic' aero profile. This is a mechanically sound example of the 'Gentleman\u2019s Agreement' era, ready for spirited canyon carving or track-day duty.",
      "price": 34500.0,
